metadata.name: Traversal #9
metadata.description:
Traversal is the marriage of two simple geometric ideas: a set of somewhat unruly, intersecting diagonal shapes, and a minimally reduced corner perspective that gives them depth.

The depicted bodies are entirely feasible as a 3D scene, and yet this composition is all about illusion. The hatch fill creates a perception of light. The dithering on the faces produces a sense of material texture. The squiggly lines imitate freehand drawing. The spatial perspective itself is achieved through a purely two-dimensional algorithm of polygon intersections and line hiding.

The original medium of my compositions is the pen plotter, and Traversal is no exception. It is entirely vector-based, and can be plotted directly. I use Paper.js to render it on-screen and as SVG.

~

To generate and download a plottable SVG file, press `S`. Please be patient; this process can take a while. The SVG can be plotted on an A5 paper. It contains two layers visible in Inkscape, so you can plot the light grey sketch lines with a different pen, or omit them altogether.

metadata.name: Migration #59
metadata.description:
"Migration" is a generative work with which I want to ease my worries about the irresponsibility of people towards the planet they live on.
If we migrate, I hope it will be for the purpose of exploring new areas and not because we have destroyed the planet we live on and are now forced to flee.

Created with 100% p5.js code and math.

Hi-res. options:

- press 'i' to save .png with resolution = 1000px x 1000px
- press 't' to save .png with resolution = 2000px x 2000px
- press 's' to save .png with resolution = 6000px x 6000px


@Mutart, July, 2022.

metadata.name: CrossWorlds #192
metadata.description:
In 2057 an error occurred in the particle accelerator machine causing a diversion in space-time that leads to duplication of our world. Scientists discovered that they can travel to these "CrossWorlds" with wormholes plagued by singularities occurring at weakened points of the fabric between worlds. In time, some worlds became hostile to each other, tried to plunder their natural resources, and take over civilizations but other worlds learned how to co-exist peacefully...
------------------
Animation_
Press R: Rotates the world 180Â°
Idle: Default animation cycles from corner to corner
Mouse: Cursor-dependent animation
MobileDevice: Controls the animation with the orientation of the device. (Android only)
------------------
Live-view_
Resolution: Add "&res=" end of your url with a resolution multiplier. (0.5-6)
Press S: Saves the current scene (Default 1600x1600 px).
Press L: Zip file containing all drawing layers separately as PNG.
Press D: Zip file containing all drawing layers separately as SVG.
------------------
Created with p5js.

metadata.name: Focussing Lightness #4
metadata.description:
In the depths of love, we search and find,
Connections that can truly bind,
Emotions run deep, and hearts entwine,
A smile, a hug, in love we confine.

Carnal pleasures may come and go,
But genuine affection, like rivers, flow,
Embrace the present, let worries fade,
In the warmth of love, our souls are made.

Sincere relationships, we seek to forge,
A path of happiness, our hearts to gorge,
In the light of others, we find our way,
From darkness and despair, we keep at bay.


Made in HydraSynth.

metadata.name: Data Overload #26
metadata.description:
This is my first project that uses shaders (so no svg export). I'm revisiting a theme that I have touched in the past: the distant cityscape against a sky representing today's urban life. The overload of information to which we are all exposed invests us like electromagnetic waves coming from a rising star causing something close to a deadly wind. The collectors can experience with form factors and palette to create the piece that best pleases their taste. Only the mode of the piece will be randomly defined with the rarest gold one, as always.
- hit s to export a '.png' file

metadata.name: Pigments #13
metadata.description:
â€œPigmentsâ€ is a generative art project that explores the beauty of optical color blending and the power of noise. 

At the heart of this work is a random composition of rectangles that are made up of dots. These pigments are arranged in multiple layers, each layer using a different color from one of the carefully curated color palettes. Each palette consists of three to five colors. 

As the pigments are shifted by random noise, new hues and patterns emerge, creating a lovely display of color and movement.

In live mode:
- Press [1]-[5] to change the resolution.
- Press [s] to save a png file at the current resolution.

This is my first generative art project. Created with p5js.

________

Looks best on high-resolution screens and viewed in live mode. When displayed on a low-resolution screen, an unintended moirÃ© pattern may appear.
